# Usage Reporting

- At the end of every assistant response, include a short `Usage` section.
- Include any usage/resources you can directly observe in-session (for example: notable API/workflow actions run, command count context, or other measurable runtime signals).
- For requested metrics you cannot directly access (for example: Cursor billing tokens, Claude account billing tokens, external account usage dashboards), omit them from the `Usage` section.
- Do not invent, estimate, or imply token/billing values when direct telemetry is unavailable.
- Keep this section concise (3-6 bullets max).
